Thought: I will start by finding the quarantined email alert from ZAP and then join it with EmailUrlInfo using the common identifier “NetworkMessageId” in order to extract the URL that the user clicked. I'll assume that the table logging the quarantined email from ZAP is called "ZAPQuarantinedEmails" (as per our hypothesis) and that the EmailUrlInfo table contains the URL details. The query is as follows.
Action: execute[SELECT eui.URL
FROM ZAPQuarantinedEmails AS zqe
JOIN EmailUrlInfo AS eui ON zqe.NetworkMessageId = eui.NetworkMessageId;
]
